class Solution {
public:
    int minSwaps(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        int count_ones = 0;
        int last_one_index = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (nums[i] == 1) {
                count_ones++;
                last_one_index = i;
            }
        }
        if (count_ones == 0 || count_ones == n) {
            return 0;
        }
        int swaps = 0;
        int current_index = 0;
        while (current_index != last_one_index) {
            current_index = (current_index + 1) % n;
            if (nums[current_index] == 1) {
                swaps++;
            }
        }
        return swaps;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW 
explanation: The solution iterates through the array once to count the number of 1's and find the index of the last 1. If all elements are 0 or 1, no swaps are needed. Otherwise, it simulates moving a 1 to its correct position by iterating through the array until it encounters the last 1. The number of iterations represents the minimum swaps required.

